														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4580409">
									

<p>Sounds to me like it would be an almost clone of X-files. Episodes that focused on specific skips would be cool if they were done right, like Kikaider said. The 096 film comes to mind when setting the standard. Alternatively, if each season was dedicated to a specific canon, that would be interesting.</p>
<p>Legally, this series could exist, however it would have to omit 173, otherwise everything can be monetized if it's credited.</p>
<p>Turning scp-5000 into a live-action show would not be a good idea though because the experience of reading that article is unique. You can't visualize anything that's happening, your imagination takes over; it's best to either come up with new skips that would do better for TV or use skips that have overarching stories.</p>

