			<div class="content" id="post-content-4630728">
									

<p><strong>My understanding of the license is limited, so take this with a grain of salt.</strong></p>
<p>Using the image of <a href="http://izumikato.com/filter/sculpture/Untitled-2004">Izumi Kato's sculpture</a> or its likeness infringes on his copyright, but the actual concept of SCP-173 as &quot;a monster that kills you if you don't look at it&quot; is free to use provided it is licensed and attributed properly. I believe any redesign would have to be clearly an original work not derived from Untitled 2004 in any way in order to be legally acceptable. This may be a grey area, but a &quot;crazy little statue&quot; sounds like it would not be a safe idea.</p>

